<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fruit" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fruit,</orth> 1) the produce of a tree or other plant in which the seeds are contained: <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.473" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 473</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.32" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 7, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.167" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.383" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 383</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 21</bibl> Collectively: <cit><quote>he dies that touches any of this f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.98" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 98</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 123</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.471" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 471</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.5.18" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.126" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.263" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 263</bibl>. Constituting the dessert at table: <cit><quote>the f. to that great feast,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 52</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) offspring, child: <bibl n="shak. luc 1064" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1064</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 97.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 97, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.214" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 214</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 43</bibl>
<lb />3) production, effect, consequence: <cit><quote>the --s of the sport,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.216" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 216</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to taste their --s of duty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 63</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 58</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 9</bibl>. <cit><quote>she took the --s of my advice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 145</bibl></cit> (== profited by my advice).
<lb />Plur. for the sing.: <cit><quote>my second joy and first --s of my body,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 98</bibl></cit> (M. Edd. <emph>first-fruits</emph>). <cit><quote>this is the --s of whoring,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 1, 116</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>fruit</emph>).
